@startuml safecrowd-engine-overview
title SafeCrowd Engine Layer Overview

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

package "application" {
  [safecrowd_app\n(Qt App)] as App
}

package "domain" {
  [safecrowd_domain\n(Scenario / Simulation / Risk)] as Domain
}

package "engine" {
  package "api" {
    [Engine API Surface\nEngineRuntime / EngineWorld /\nWorldQuery / WorldResources /\nWorldCommands / EngineSystem] as Api
  }

  [Runtime Core\n(FrameClock / SystemScheduler /\nCommandBuffer / ResourceStore /\nDeterministicRng)] as Runtime
  [ECS Core\n(EcsCore / EntityRegistry /\nComponentRegistry / PackedComponentStorage)] as Ecs
}

App --> Domain
Domain --> Api : configure / run / query / queue mutations
App ..> Api : optional viewport bridge

Api --> Runtime : owns execution flow
Api --> Ecs : owns world data facade
Runtime --> Ecs : through EngineWorld facade

note bottom of Api
  Shared engine API surface.
  Domain systems and runtime both
  meet at EngineWorld here through
  query / resources / commands facets.
  Mutation requests are deferred first
  and committed by the runtime later.
end note

note bottom of Runtime
  Time, phase order, deferred mutation,
  deterministic random streams,
  and execution orchestration.
  Initial engine scope prioritizes
  fixed-step scheduling over advanced
  event or snapshot extensions.
end note

note bottom of Ecs
  Dense storage, generation-safe entities,
  and signature matching.
  Domain-specific behavior does not live here.
end note

@enduml
